m.n: A Bitter Means to the Bitter End
m.de: In a bid to sabotage the Braithwaite's rival moonshine operation, Maggie asks you to taint their stills and sour their latest batch.
Samson asked you to find him at the gallows in Saint Denis. You have a bank to rob.
Barbarella Alcazar
Lem is being transported to Sisika Penitentiary. Ambush the convoy, break Lem out, and get him back to Maggie.
Marshal Davies has requested your assistance. ~n~~n~Alfredo Montez's men are about to turn Valentine upside down looking for him.
Cecil C. Tucker
Lem has sourced some important new ingredients for your moonshine operation and is bringing them in by boat. ~n~~n~Maggie asks you to meet him at the docks to make sure the delivery goes smoothly.
Horley needs to see you. He and Mrs. LeClerk are due to meet Amos Lancing in Blackwater and will require protection.
Etta Doyle

The Night Stalkers are supernaturally fast, tough and strong, but their powers are bound to the skull masks dotted around their lands. The more masks the Hunters steal, the weaker the Night Stalkers become, while the Hunters' own weapons grow stronger. The Hunters can only win by stealing every mask, and then eliminating every Night Stalker. The Night Stalkers can win by killing all of the Hunters, or surviving until the time limit.~n~~n~2 Teams~n~Forced Weapons~n~No Manual Respawns
